# DII-CAMT ShowPro: Comprehensive Backend Specification

This document serves as the complete technical blueprint for the backend implementation of the DII-CAMT ShowPro project. It defines the roles, systems, database schema, and API requirements based on the existing React + TypeScript frontend.

---

## 1. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

The system operates with 5 distinct roles, each with specific navigation and data access requirements:

| Role | Core Responsibilities | Key Pages/Modules |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Student** | Skills & Portfolio building, Internship tracking | Portfolio, Grades, Activities, Internships, Requests, Messages |
| **Lecturer** | Academic delivery, Student advising | Teaching Schedule, Advisee List, Grading, Appointments, Workload |
| **Staff** | Administrative operations | User Mgmt, Budget, Personnel, Document Issuance, Room Mgmt |
| **Company** | Talent recruitment & Internship evaluation | Job Postings, Student Search, Applicant Mgmt, Intern Tracking |
| **Admin** | System integrity & Global oversight | Audit Logs, System Settings, Reports, Full User/Course Access |

---

## 2. Database Specification (Prisma Model)

Based on `src/types/index.ts`, the database should implement the following core models:

### Core Identity
- **User:** Stores `id`, `email`, `password_hash`, `name`, `nameThai`, `role`, `avatar`, `isActive`.
- **StudentProfile:** Linked to User. Stores `studentId`, `major`, `year`, `gpax`, `earnedCredits`, `advisorId`.
- **LecturerProfile:** Linked to User. Stores `lecturerId`, `department`, `position`, `specialization`.
- **CompanyProfile:** Linked to User. Stores `companyName`, `industry`, `size`, `website`.

### Academic & Skills
- **Course:** `code`, `name`, `credits`, `semester`, `academicYear`, `lecturerId`.
- **Enrollment:** Link table for `Student` and `Course` with `grade` and `status`.
- **Skill:** `name`, `category`, `level`, `verifiedBy`.
- **Portfolio:** Linked to Student. Contains `summary`, `projects` (JSON/Relation), `githubUrl`.

### Workflow & Communication
- **Activity:** `title`, `type`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `gamificationPoints`, `activityHours`.
- **JobPosting:** `title`, `type`, `companyId`, `requirements`, `salary`, `status`.
- **Application:** Link between `Student` and `JobPosting` with `status`, `resumeUrl`.
- **Appointment:** `studentId`, `lecturerId`, `date`, `purpose`, `status`.
- **Notification:** `recipientId`, `title`, `message`, `type`, `isRead`.

